{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33",
    "translationId": "vulgate",
    "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
    "chapterNumber": 33,
    "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33",
    "summary": "Source text for Deuteronomy 33 in Clementine Vulgate."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.1",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:1",
      "text": "Hæc est benedictio, qua benedixit Moyses, homo Dei, filiis Israël ante mortem suam.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.2",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:2",
      "text": "Et ait: Dominus de Sinai venit, et de Seir ortus est nobis: apparuit de monte Pharan, et cum eo sanctorum millia. In dextera ejus ignea lex.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.3",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:3",
      "text": "Dilexit populos, omnes sancti in manu illius sunt: et qui appropinquant pedibus ejus, accipient de doctrina illius.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.4",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:4",
      "text": "Legem præcepit nobis Moyses, hæreditatem multitudinis Jacob.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.5",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:5",
      "text": "Erit apud rectissimum rex, congregatis principibus populi cum tribubus Israël.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.6",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:6",
      "text": "Vivat Ruben, et non moriatur, et sit parvus in numero.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.7",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:7",
      "text": "Hæc est Judæ benedictio: Audi, Domine, vocem Judæ, et ad populum suum introduc eum: manus ejus pugnabunt pro eo, et adjutor illius contra adversarios ejus erit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.8",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:8",
      "text": "Levi quoque ait: Perfectio tua, et doctrina tua viro sancto tuo, quem probasti in tentatione, et judicasti ad aquas contradictionis.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.9",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:9",
      "text": "Qui dixit patri suo et matri suæ: Nescio vos: et fratribus suis: Ignoro vos: et nescierunt filios suos. Hi custodierunt eloquium tuum, et pactum tuum servaverunt.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.10",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:10",
      "text": "Judicia tua, o Jacob, et legem tuam, o Israël: ponent thymiama in furore tuo, et holocaustum super altare tuum.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.11",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:11",
      "text": "Benedic, Domine, fortitudini ejus: et opera manuum illius suscipe. Percute dorsa inimicorum ejus: et qui oderunt eum, non consurgant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.12",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:12",
      "text": "Et Benjamin ait: Amantissimus Domini habitabit confidenter in eo: quasi in thalamo tota die morabitur, et inter humeros illius requiescet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.13",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:13",
      "text": "Joseph quoque ait: De benedictione Domini terra ejus, de pomis cæli, et rore, atque abysso subjacente.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.14",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:14",
      "text": "De pomis fructuum solis ac lunæ,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.15",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:15",
      "text": "de vertice antiquorum montium, de pomis collium æternorum:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.16",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:16",
      "text": "et de frugibus terræ, et de plenitudine ejus. Benedictio illius qui apparuit in rubo, veniat super caput Joseph, et super verticem nazaræi inter fratres suos.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.17",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:17",
      "text": "Quasi primogeniti tauri pulchritudo ejus, cornua rhinocerotis cornua illius: in ipsis ventilabit gentes usque ad terminos terræ. Hæ sunt multitudines Ephraim: et hæc millia Manasse.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.18",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:18",
      "text": "Et Zabulon ait: Lætare, Zabulon, in exitu tuo, et Issachar in tabernaculis tuis.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.19",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:19",
      "text": "Populos vocabunt ad montem: ibi immolabunt victimas justitiæ. Qui inundationem maris quasi lac sugent, et thesauros absconditos arenarum.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.20",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:20",
      "text": "Et Gad ait: Benedictus in latitudine Gad: quasi leo requievit, cepitque brachium et verticem.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.21",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:21",
      "text": "Et vidit principatum suum, quod in parte sua doctor esset repositus: qui fuit cum principibus populi, et fecit justitias Domini, et judicium suum cum Israël.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.22",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:22",
      "text": "Dan quoque ait: Dan catulus leonis, fluet largiter de Basan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.23",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:23",
      "text": "Et Nephthali dixit: Nephthali abundantia perfruetur, et plenus erit benedictionibus Domini: mare et meridiem possidebit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.24",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:24",
      "text": "Aser quoque ait: Benedictus in filiis Aser, sit placens fratribus suis, et tingat in oleo pedem suum:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.25",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:25",
      "text": "ferrum et æs calceamentum ejus. Sicut dies juventutis tuæ, ita et senectus tua.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.26",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:26",
      "text": "Non est deus alius ut Deus rectissimi, ascensor cæli, auxiliator tuus. Magnificentia ejus discurrunt nubes,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.27",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:27",
      "text": "habitaculum ejus sursum, et subter brachia sempiterna ejiciet a facie tua inimicum, dicetque: Conterere.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.28",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:28",
      "text": "Habitabit Israël confidenter, et solus. Oculus Jacob in terra frumenti et vini, cælique caligabunt rore.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "vulgate:deuteronomy.33.29",
      "translationId": "vulgate",
      "bookSlug": "deuteronomy",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Deuteronomy 33:29",
      "text": "Beatus es tu, Israël: quis similis tui, popule, qui salvaris in Domino? Scutum auxilii tui, et gladius gloriæ tuæ: negabunt te inimici tui, et tu eorum colla calcabis.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
